The paper deals with designing temporal description logics for reasoning about temporal conceptual data models, which involves aspects of artificial intelligence (AI) and databases (DB). The use of description logics (DL) also suggests a connection to logic (LO) and formal methods. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the logics, which could fall under machine learning (LG) or computational linguistics (CL).
